node.text:
Joyful time☀️ You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @nomadfervor

“Life is precious because you can’t watch it again, once you realise you aren’t gonna be around forever, that’s what makes life so magical” 🥰

📽 @twosometravellers
📍Australia

node.text:
Waterproof boy 🦎 We can post your photos in our account, follow the link in our bio: @nomadfervor and we will select your pictures

📽 @simplygecko.co

This is a really cool aspect of gecko skin. The water is not actually touching their scales, but is coming into contact with air that is trapped in between tiny hair follicles called spinules. These follicles suspend the water so they can't flatten out over the surface area of the skin. They are less than a thousandth of a millimeter apart, and make geckos almost waterproof.

Icelandic summer collection 😍 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting nomadfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @nomadfervor
